    <p>
      As a student of media theory, it felt like the current socio-political landscape was asking a lot of questions.
      If in the 70s, broadcast media changed the structure of the domestic space, 50 years later, in the 2020s, social
      media is changing the structure of democracies and bodies (and the kind of machines we make).
      <br>
      <br>
      So for this work, the techniques that I use for sound synthesis, I applied those techniques to media streams –
      to observe, investigate and study the streams of media that surround us.
      <br>
      <br>
      What I am thinking about is - what kind of tools do artists and people in general have to investigate this
      vectorized media and data in its various forms. What kind of mental models do we need to be able to tear it
      apart from profit motive and weaponization.

    </p>
